'''Brice Lauriche Samba''' (born 25 April 1994) is a professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Goalkeeper (association football)|goalkeeper]] for [[Ligue 1]] club [[Stade Rennais FC|Rennes]]. Born in the Republic of the Congo, he plays for the [[France national football team|France national team]].

==Club career==
===Le Havre===
Samba joined [[Le Havre AC|Le Havre]] in 2006, working his way through their youth teams before appearing in the first-team in 2011.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.francefootball.fr/news/Ligue-1-brice-samba-caen-raconte-les-anecdotes-et-moments-de-sa-carriere-quand-tu-es-a-marseille-ta-vie-change/836394|title=Ligue 1 : Brice Samba (Caen) raconte les anecdotes et moments de sa carrière, "Quand tu es à Marseille, ta vie change"|website=France Football}}</ref>

===Marseille===
[[File:Valais Cup 2013 - OM-FC Porto 13-07-2013 - Brice Samba en extension (cropped2).jpg|thumb|Samba in action with Marseille in the 2013 Valais Cup]]
On 4 January 2013, Samba joined [[Olympique de Marseille|Marseille]] from Le Havre, signing a four-and-a-half-year contract. He made his professional debut for Marseille on 5 January 2014 in a [[Coupe de France]] game against [[Stade de Reims|Reims]] keeping a clean sheet in a 2–0 home win.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2014/01/05/france/coupe-de-france/olympique-de-marseille/stade-de-reims/1605908/?ICID=HP_MS_01_16|title=Olympique Marseille vs. Reims - 5 January 2014 - Soccerway|website=Int.soccerway.com|accessdate=14 July 2018}}</ref> On 9 July 2015, Samba joined [[AS Nancy Lorraine|Nancy]] on a season-long loan.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.lephoceen.fr/infos-om/mercato/officiel-brice-samba-prete-a-nancy-138372|title=Officiel : Brice Samba prêté à Nancy|first=Le|last=Phocéen|date=9 July 2015|website=Le Phocéen}}</ref>

===Caen===
Samba joined [[SM Caen|Caen]] on a four-year deal from [[Olympique de Marseille|Marseille]] on 30 June 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.smcaen.fr/2017-2018/actualites/groupe-pro/brice-samba-un-nouveau-gardien-au-smc|title=Brice Samba, un nouveau gardien au SMC|date=30 June 2017|website=Stade Malherbe Caen}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.getfootballnewsfrance.com/2017/official-sm-caen-pick-up-goalkeeper-brice-samba/|title=Official &#124; SM Caen pick up goalkeeper Brice Samba &#124; Get French Football News|website=getfootballnewsfrance.com|date=3 July 2017 }}</ref>

===Nottingham Forest===
On 7 August 2019, Samba joined [[EFL Championship]] side [[Nottingham Forest F.C.|Nottingham Forest]] on a four-year deal for an undisclosed fee.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.smcaen.fr/2019-2020/actualites/groupe-pro/brice-samba-rejoint-nottingham-forest|title=Brice Samba rejoint Nottingham Forest|date=7 August 2019|website=Stade Malherbe Caen}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nottinghamforest.co.uk/news/2019/august/samba-signs/|title=Samba signs|website=nottinghamforest.co.uk}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/49268427|title=Brice Samba: Nottingham Forest sign goalkeeper from French side Caen|work=BBC Sport |date=7 August 2019}}</ref> He was initially brought in as a backup for on loan goalkeeper [[Arijanet Muric]], but earned his place as Forest's number one after Muric made a number of costly mistakes.<ref>{{cite news|last=Taylor|first=Paul|title=Samba is showing fans that Forest were right to add yet another keeper to their books|url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/1270973/2019/10/07/samba-proving-his-worth-and-showing-fans-that-forest-were-right-to-add-yet-another-keeper-to-their-books/|access-date=16 October 2020|website=The Athletic}}</ref>

Samba made his debut for Forest on 13 August 2019 in a 1–0 [[EFL Cup]] victory over [[Fleetwood Town F.C.|Fleetwood Town]].<ref>{{Cite news|title=Forest beat Fleetwood to reach round two|language=en-GB|work=BBC Sport|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/49245384|access-date=16 October 2020}}</ref> His league debut came on 24 August 2019 in a 2–1 win against [[Fulham F.C.|Fulham]].{{Citation needed|date=March 2023}} His impressive performances led him being named the Championship Fans' Player of the Month for November 2019.<ref name=":2">{{cite web |date=4 December 2019 |title=Samba clinches Player of the Month award |url=https://www.nottinghamforest.co.uk/news/2019/december/brice-samba-clinches-player-of-the-month-award/ |accessdate=1 December 2020 |website=Nottingham Forest}}</ref> On 8 September 2020, Samba was included in the [[Professional Footballers' Association|PFA]] Championship Team of the Year for the 2019–20 season.<ref name="autogenerated1">{{cite tweet |author=Professional Footballers' Association |author-link=Professional Footballers' Association |user=PFA |number=1303394671494914049 |date=8 September 2020 |title=A massive congratulations to these players, for earning a place in the 2020 PFA Championship Team of the Year. #TOTY #PFAawards https://t.co/1DEGUXATbG |language=en |access-date=22 January 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200908180851/https://twitter.com/PFA/status/1303394671494914049 |archive-date=8 September 2020 |url-status=live}}</ref>

In the [[2022 English Football League play-offs#Championship|2022 Championship play-off semi-final]], Samba saved three penalties to send Forest through to the final against [[Huddersfield Town]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/61389080|title=Nottingham Forest v Sheffield United |work=BBC Sport |access-date=18 May 2022}}</ref> He subsequently started in the [[2022 EFL Championship play-off final]] before being substituted for [[Ethan Horvath]] in the 90th minute with a groin injury as Forest held on to a 1–0 lead to confirm their return to the [[Premier League]] for first time in 23 years.<ref name="autogenerated2">{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/61539298|title=Forest return to Premier League after 23-year wait|work=BBC Sport |access-date=30 May 2022|date=29 May 2022}}</ref>

===Lens===
On 5 July 2022, it was announced that Samba had signed a five-year contract with [[Ligue 1]] club [[RC Lens|Lens]] for an undisclosed fee.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.nottinghamforest.co.uk/news/2022/july/05/samba-departs-for-lens/ | title=Samba departs for Lens | date=5 July 2022 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|author=rclens.fr |url=https://www.rclens.fr/fr/news/mercato-contrat-brice-samba-rclens-20220705 |title=Brice Samba, de l'explosivité dans les buts &#124; RC Lens |language=fr |publisher=Rclens.fr |date= |accessdate=2022-09-15}}</ref> In the first half of the [[2022–23 Ligue 1]] season, he had 9 clean sheets out of 19 games.<ref>{{Cite web |title=L'équipe type de la première moitié de saison en Ligue 1 avec Messi, Neymar et Cabella |url=https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/Article/L-equipe-type-de-la-premiere-moitie-de-saison-en-ligue-1-avec-messi-neymar-et-cabella/1376451 |access-date=2023-01-25 |website=L'Équipe |language=fr}}</ref> He ended the season with 15 clean sheets out of 38 league matches, the highest in the season and was awarded the [[Trophées UNFP du football#Goalkeeper of the Year|Ligue 1 Goalkeeper of the Year]] whilst being named in the [[Union Nationale des Footballeurs Professionnels|UNFP]] Ligue 1 [[Trophées UNFP du football#Team of the Year|Team of the Year]].<ref name=":1" /><ref name=":0" /> He conceded the least goals (29 goals) in the league helping Lens to place second with 84 points, one point behind league winners [[Paris Saint-Germain F.C.|Paris Saint-Germain]] and secure a champions league spot for the first time in 20 years since 2002–03 season and the third time in the club's history.<ref>{{Cite web |date=3 June 2023 |title=RC Lens Secure UEFA Champions League Spot with Victory over Auxerre |url=https://www.beinsports.com/us/ligue-1/video/rc-lens-secure-uefa-champions-league-spot-wit/2106085 |access-date=5 June 2023 |website=beIN SPORTS USA}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Wills |first=S. |date=2 June 2023 |title=RC Lens look to join exclusive club |url=https://www.ligue1.com/Articles/News/2023/06/02/rc-lens-look-to-join-exclusive-club |access-date=4 June 2023 |website=Ligue1 COM}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Scott |first=A. |date=4 June 2023 |title=Remarkable season takes Lens to promised land |url=https://www.ligue1.com/Articles/Opinion/2023/06/03/remarkable-season-takes-lens-to-promised-land-haise-fofana-samba-danso-openda |access-date=4 June 2023 |website=Ligue1 COM}}</ref>

==International career==
Born in the [[Republic of the Congo]], Samba holds both Congolese and [[France|French]] nationalities.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Brice SAMBA - |url=https://www.unfp.org/joueur/brice-samba-17430/ |access-date=2023-08-02 |website=www.unfp.org}}</ref>

In March 2023, he received his first call-up to the [[France national football team|France senior national team]] for the [[UEFA Euro 2024 qualifying]] matches against the [[Netherlands national football team|Netherlands]] and the [[Republic of Ireland national football team|Republic of Ireland]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=Thuram and Samba in France squad |url=https://www.ligue1.com/Articles/News/2023/03/16/thuram-and-samba-in-france-squad |access-date=17 March 2023 |website=Ligue 1 |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=16 March 2023 |title=La liste des vingt-trois Bleus |url=https://www.fff.fr/article/9853-la-liste-des-vingt-trois-bleus.html |access-date=17 March 2023 |website=FFF |language=fr-FR}}</ref>

On 16 June 2023, he made his debut playing the whole game in a [[UEFA Euro 2024 qualifying]] match against [[Gibraltar national football team|Gibraltar]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/match-direct/qualif-euro/2024/gibraltar-france-live/555450|title=Gibraltar - France, le résumé du match|trans-title=Gibraltar - France, match summary|language=fr|publisher=L'Équipe|date=16 June 2023|access-date=4 October 2023}}</ref>

On 11 May 2026, he was named in the France squad for the [[2026 FIFA World Cup]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=Mbappe highlights all-star France World Cup squad {{!}} Didier Deschamps has chosen his 26-man squad ahead of the tournament in Canada, Mexico and USA. |url=https://www.fifa.com/en/tournaments/mens/worldcup/canadamexicousa2026/articles/france-world-cup-squad-named |access-date=2026-05-27 |website=www.fifa.com}}</ref>

